1
00:00:07,879 --> 00:00:09,400
What we can confirm now is

2
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:11,279
the nail fragment in the fish's belly

3
00:00:11,439 --> 00:00:13,119
matches Chen Yongjiang's biometrics.

4
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:14,279
On top of that, recently

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,760
our surveillance on him has turned up nothing.

6
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,160
We can basically conclude

7
00:00:18,559 --> 00:00:20,640
that suspect Chen Yongjiang is dead,

8
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:22,839
and most likely was dismembered

9
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,120
and dumped into the sea.

10
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,000
As of now,

11
00:00:27,320 --> 00:00:29,239
Luo Xiao is the most likely killer.

12
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,000
But we lack hard evidence.

13
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:32,439
We're still stuck here.

14
00:00:34,799 --> 00:00:36,399
From the initial Xin Qili case

15
00:00:36,799 --> 00:00:38,960
to now, with several lives at stake,

16
00:00:39,119 --> 00:00:40,000
violent confrontations,

17
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:42,640
plus the financial crime chain behind it,

18
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:45,240
this is an unprecedentedly complex case.

19
00:00:45,679 --> 00:00:48,359
If Luo Xiao is the mastermind behind it,

20
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,920
then what we're about to face

21
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,799
is a lawyer skilled in counter-investigation.

22
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,119
He knows exactly how, at a crime scene,

23
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:56,640
to leave no evidence of his crime.

24
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:58,280
He knows how to exploit the law

25
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,479
to absolve himself.

26
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,479
He even knows how we'll question him,

27
00:01:01,479 --> 00:01:02,280
and what we'll ask.

28
00:01:02,399 --> 00:01:03,799
He has his own scripted answers ready.

29
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,480
So, when facing him,

30
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:07,959
we have to be on full alert.

31
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,519
Talk.

32
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:58,000
I tied Chen Yongjiang up right here,

33
00:01:58,159 --> 00:02:01,719
then dismembered him with a chainsaw.

34
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,799
Piece by piece.

35
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,760
Then I ground them up in an ice crusher,

36
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,599
and dumped it in the sea.

37
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:07,879
Which ice crusher?

38
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,120
Point it out properly.

39
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:17,120
What about the chainsaw?

40
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,199
Dumped it in the sea.

41
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:20,759
How long did the sawing take?

42
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,520
About an hour, I guess.

43
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:27,759
Your boat was over there.

44
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:29,960
How did you charge the chainsaw?

45
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,919
I charged it before coming.

46
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:36,919
A cordless chainsaw lasts half an hour max.

47
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,400
Then I might be remembering wrong.

48
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,360
Anyway, that's how it went down.

49
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,759
The chainsaw must've sprayed everywhere.

50
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,439
It would've sprayed all over.

51
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,719
How did you deal with that?

52
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:51,319
I poured sulfuric acid on it.

53
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:52,319
Poured it everywhere.

54
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:54,120
Doused the whole place.

55
00:02:54,439 --> 00:02:55,439
You're quite capable, aren't you?

56
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,879
And you're pretty proud of it, huh?

57
00:02:57,759 --> 00:02:59,240
Let's go. Take us to the shore to point it out.

58
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,400
Chief Wang.

59
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:11,680
He's clearly just—

60
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,840
Let's get the on-site identification first.

61
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:30,000
That kid wasn't telling the truth.

62
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,199
Did you check on the lawyer?

63
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,560
Yes, Bai Qiming.

64
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:35,759
He used to handle criminal cases.

65
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:38,000
No unusual connections so far.

66
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:39,360
Who brought him in?

67
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,560
Min Shengquan's mother.

68
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:46,080
He used her to make Min recant.

69
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,759
So if that's the case,

70
00:03:47,759 --> 00:03:49,639
the severed finger at Min's place,

71
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,759
and the contract scene too,

72
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:52,039
are basically all fabricated.

73
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:54,840
That means

74
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:56,240
the people behind this are no joke.

75
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:57,960
Did you meet Min Shengquan's mother?

76
00:03:59,719 --> 00:04:00,280
I'll go now.

77
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:12,719
In this world, no worries...

78
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:14,759
Uncle Ma, you've been singing all day.

79
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:16,480
Can you give it a rest?

80
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,279
Give it a rest?

81
00:04:20,639 --> 00:04:21,959
Then I'll give you something quieter.

82
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:24,480
Let me do a bit of Pingju opera.

83
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:32,079
Three cannon blasts outside the gate...

84
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:33,879
Keep it down, keep it down!

85
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:39,319
Ma'am.

86
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,000
Ma'am.

87
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:45,480
You mean me?

88
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,160
Yes.

89
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,160
Um, hello.

90
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:50,079
Min Shengquan is your son, right?

91
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,560
Yes.

92
00:04:51,639 --> 00:04:52,199
Don't be nervous.

93
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,000
We're with the police.

94
00:04:53,079 --> 00:04:54,279
We'd like to ask you a few things.

95
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,879
Then, shall we talk inside?

96
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:59,279
No need, just a quick chat.

97
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,439
You hired Min Shengquan's lawyer?

98
00:05:02,639 --> 00:05:03,600
Yes.

99
00:05:03,879 --> 00:05:05,839
How did you find this Lawyer Bai?

100
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:08,199
A day later,

101
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:11,199
A young man from Min's shop

102
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,199
came to find me.

103
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,160
He told me Min had been arrested,

104
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,040
and to hire a lawyer quickly.

105
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,439
That's how I found out.

106
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,600
So I rushed to ask neighbors for help,

107
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:23,120
and they recommended him.

108
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
They said the fee was low,

109
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:28,360
and that he does pro bono work.

110
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:31,480
I said, as long as he saves my son,

111
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,560
I'd pay any amount.

112
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,360
Neighbor?

113
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,680
What does this neighbor do?

114
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,519
Do you know?

115
00:05:38,959 --> 00:05:40,360
You mean the one who recommended him?

116
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:40,959
Yes.

117
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,560
That's Xiao Chen.

118
00:05:42,839 --> 00:05:44,000
He's such a nice guy.

119
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:45,560
Really good-hearted.

120
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:47,839
When did you meet Lawyer Bai then?

121
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,120
I never met him.

122
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,920
Because Xiao Chen hired him for me.

123
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:56,680
I was afraid I couldn't explain things well,

124
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,439
so I had Xiao Chen speak for me.

125
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,639
Xiao Chen...

126
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:03,399
What's his full name?

127
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,959
Chen what? Do you remember?

128
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,959
He said his name was Chen...

129
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,000
Chen...

130
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,519
Wait, his surname isn't Chen.

131
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,319
Everyone around here calls him Xiao Chen.

132
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,800
It just became a habit.

133
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:21,279
I can't even remember his surname now.

134
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:25,240
Not Chen, it's Ruan.

135
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:27,439
Right, Ruan.

136
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,399
Ruan Chen, that's it.

137
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:32,639
He reads fortunes at the temple.

138
00:06:46,759 --> 00:06:47,839
Mr. Ruan?

139
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:50,319
He went to buy groceries.

140
00:07:09,879 --> 00:07:10,879
Lawyer Luo.

141
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,480
Where's Mr. Ruan?

142
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,959
He'd like to invite you for a meal.

143
00:07:44,079 --> 00:07:45,279
Godfather, he's here.

144
00:07:57,439 --> 00:07:58,279
Mr. Ruan.

145
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,360
You're here, Lawyer Luo.

146
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,879
Come, have some tea.

147
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:09,680
Have a seat.

148
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:20,439
No need to be so tense.

149
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,399
I invited you today

150
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,079
not just for tea,

151
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,160
but to congratulate you on completing...

152
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,759
Brother Mao's unfinished business.

153
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,799
Did Brother Mao

154
00:08:34,519 --> 00:08:35,720
use to come here too?

155
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,200
You've surpassed

156
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,519
Brother Mao by far.

157
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,559
Thanks for the flattery.

158
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,639
I really do approve of you.

159
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:50,799
I never expected

160
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,399
the Fengmao line could keep running.

161
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,320
And under the police's pursuit, no less.

162
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:00,799
The speed also caught me off guard.

163
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,679
So today,

164
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,320
besides congratulating you,

165
00:09:05,799 --> 00:09:07,080
I want to offer you an opportunity.

166
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,200
What, you mean

167
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,279
to pour your tea?

168
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,240
Or be your driver?

169
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,039
Lawyer Luo,

170
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:21,519
you're joking.

171
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:24,759
You want me to launder money for you,

172
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:26,360
right?

173
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:28,720
What if...

174
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,080
What if I say no?

175
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,080
What reason do you have to refuse?

176
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:38,360
What reason do I have to accept?

177
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,799
Because this time,

178
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:49,399
the money I need you to launder

179
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,759
is a lot.

180
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:52,759
A lot.

181
00:09:53,799 --> 00:09:54,759
How much?

182
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,919
A lot means...

183
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,200
one billion.

184
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:33,399
Mr. Ruan,

185
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:36,320
you really think highly of me.

186
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:40,080
One billion.

187
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,639
Do you even know

188
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:44,399
what one billion means?

189
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:47,159
How could I possibly agree?

190
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,000
One billion...

191
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,080
I really don't know what that means.

192
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:57,960
But here's 30 million,

193
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,720
clean and legitimate money.

194
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:05,200
It's the operating capital for you.

195
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:08,320
The rest to be laundered is overseas.

196
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,759
But don't worry, Lawyer Luo,

197
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,120
you can take your time.

198
00:11:17,399 --> 00:11:18,279
I can't do it.

199
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,960
I can't launder a single cent.

200
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:26,879
Chief Wang.

201
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,799
Min Shengquan suddenly recanted.

202
00:11:28,799 --> 00:11:30,679
Most likely coached by that lawyer.

203
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:31,879
You saw it on the scene yourself.

204
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,559
His on-site testimony and identification

205
00:11:33,559 --> 00:11:34,440
were riddled with holes.

206
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,799
We can't just close the case like this.

207
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:41,320
Chief Wang.

208
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:42,000
About this matter...

209
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:42,919
Close the door.

210
00:11:46,279 --> 00:11:48,320
Look, first of all, this Min Shengquan,

211
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,240
his dismemberment story is suspicious.

212
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,080
He said he got a few of his men,

213
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,080
and then they found Chen Yongjiang at the dock,

214
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:54,919
hiding in a corner.

215
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,960
and dismembered him at a warehouse.

216
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,000
How is that even possible?

217
00:11:58,159 --> 00:11:59,000
Our colleagues

218
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,159
worked around the clock checking footage,

219
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:01,919
and found no leads at all.

220
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,320
Yet his few men just found him?

221
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,440
We must keep investigating Min Shengquan.

222
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,120
But throwing Molotov cocktails

223
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,600
into a residential home

224
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,720
had a huge social impact.

225
00:12:17,399 --> 00:12:19,080
Especially that video from the scene,

226
00:12:19,519 --> 00:12:22,200
it's spreading fast and wide online.

227
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:24,519
This matter

228
00:12:24,879 --> 00:12:26,360
must be resolved as soon as possible,

229
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,799
to give the public an answer.

230
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:32,399
Regarding Min Shengquan's testimony,

231
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,720
the contradictions raise doubts.

232
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,200
We need to keep investigating him.

233
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,960
If he really was

234
00:12:41,399 --> 00:12:43,720
coerced into changing his testimony,

235
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:45,759
then it's possible

236
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:47,399
that behind him,

237
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:50,320
there's a much bigger power at play.

238
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,440
You're absolutely right.

239
00:12:53,279 --> 00:12:54,279
The focus now

240
00:12:54,759 --> 00:12:56,320
isn't how Chen Yongjiang died,

241
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,759
but what power stands behind him,

242
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,080
and who those people are.

243
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,440
There's one lead now

244
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,360
that can connect all these cases.

245
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,000
The Fengmao Company's accounts.

246
00:13:09,399 --> 00:13:11,320
After our investigations these past days,

247
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,840
one thing we can confirm

248
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,600
is that Chen Yongjiang killing Xin Qili,

249
00:13:14,679 --> 00:13:16,919
is a completely fabricated motive.

250
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:18,879
Also, Min Shengquan

251
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:20,519
said he killed Chen Yongjiang

252
00:13:20,519 --> 00:13:22,080
to swallow up his company.

253
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,559
That doesn't hold up either.

254
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:25,320
If he wanted cash, sure,

255
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,559
right?

256
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:28,120
But to take over Fengmao Company,

257
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,960
he'd have to go through legal procedures,

258
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,320
and do share transfers.

259
00:13:31,799 --> 00:13:33,000
What kind of society do we live in now?

260
00:13:33,159 --> 00:13:34,919
Min Shengquan is a business owner too.

261
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,600
Killing someone to take over a company,

262
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:39,320
he wouldn't do something like that easily.

263
00:13:40,039 --> 00:13:42,200
Even if all our speculations

264
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:44,279
have doubts at every turn,

265
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,240
money never lies.

266
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,679
So I had Zhao Dian check Fengmao's books.

267
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,360
The transactions do show anomalies,

268
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:52,879
involving money laundering activity.

269
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:55,559
But which specific transactions,

270
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,080
and the nature of those anomalies,

271
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,720
we're short on manpower right now.

272
00:14:01,879 --> 00:14:03,200
I support your judgment.

273
00:14:03,799 --> 00:14:05,159
Do a deeper investigation.

274
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:07,639
The city's economic crimes unit

275
00:14:07,799 --> 00:14:09,399
is coming to our county bureau in a few days

276
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,720
to investigate an economic crime case

277
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,440
related to Xin Qili.

278
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,240
I want to use this opportunity

279
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:20,039
to join forces with them,

280
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,240
so this case

281
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,879
can achieve a further breakthrough.

282
00:14:26,759 --> 00:14:27,480
Brother Xiao.

283
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,320
Now Min can't get out either.

284
